## 2. LOGIN USER
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.tech@gearguard.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123!"
}

### ✅ Response:
# Same structure as register
# Returns new token pair each time

---

## 3. GET CURRENT USER (Protected Route)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN>

### ✅ Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Current user fetched successfully",
#   "data": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "name": "John Technician",
#     "email": "john.tech@gearguard.com",
#     "role": "Technician",
#     "isActive": true,
#     "team": {
#       "id": 2,
#       "name": "Electrical Team",
#       "specialization": "Electricians"
#     },
#     "createdAt": "2024-03-15T10:00:00.000Z",
#     "updatedAt": "2024-03-15T10:00:00.000Z"
#   }
# }

---

## 4. REFRESH ACCESS TOKEN
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..."
}

### ✅ Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Token refreshed successfully",
#   "data": {
#     "accessToken": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
#     "expiresIn": "7d"
#   }
# }

---

## 5. LOGOUT (Protected Route)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN>

### ✅ Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Logout successful. Please discard tokens on client side."
# }

---

## 6. ACCESS PROTECTED ENDPOINT (Example: Get All Equipment)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/equipment
Authorization: Bearer <ACCESS_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN>

### ✅ Response:
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Equipment retrieved successfully",
#   "data": [
#     {
#       "id": 1,
#       "name": "CNC Machine",
#       "serialNumber": "CNC-001",
#       "category": "Machinery",
#       ...
#     }
#   ]
# }

### ❌ Error Response (No Token):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "No token provided. Please include Authorization header: Bearer <token>"
# }
# Status: 401 Unauthorized

### ❌ Error Response (Invalid Token):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "Invalid or expired token"
# }
# Status: 401 Unauthorized

---

## 7. ERROR: Invalid Credentials
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.tech@gearguard.com",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}

### ❌ Response:
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "Invalid email or password"
# }
# Status: 401 Unauthorized

---

## 8. ERROR: User Already Exists
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another Name",
  "email": "john.tech@gearguard.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### ❌ Response:
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "User with this email already exists"
# }
# Status: 400 Bad Request

---

## 9. ERROR: Deactivated User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "deactivated@gearguard.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### ❌ Response:
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "Your account has been deactivated"
# }
# Status: 403 Forbidden

---

## TOKEN STRUCTURE EXAMPLES

### Access Token (JWT Format)
```
Header: {
  "alg": "HS256",
  "typ": "JWT"
}

Payload: {
  "id": 1,
  "email": "john.tech@gearguard.com",
  "role": "Technician",
  "type": "access",
  "iat": 1678886400,
  "exp": 1679491200,
  "iss": "gearguard-api",
  "aud": "gearguard-frontend"
}

Signature: HMACSHA256(base64UrlEncode(header) + "." + base64UrlEncode(payload), JWT_SECRET)
```

**Decoded Online**: Visit https://jwt.io/ and paste your token

---

## POSTMAN SETUP GUIDE

### Step 1: Create Collection Variable
1. Open Postman
2. Create collection: "GearGuard JWT"
3. Go to Variables tab
4. Add variables:
   ```
   - accessToken = (empty, will be set by login)
   - refreshToken = (empty, will be set by login)
   - baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
   ```

### Step 2: Set Up Authorization Globally
1. Click "Edit" on collection
2. Go to Authorization tab
3. Type: Bearer Token
4. Token: {{accessToken}}

### Step 3: Create Login Request
1. POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
2. After successful response:
3. Tests tab, add:
```javascript
if (pm.response.code === 200) {
  pm.environment.set("accessToken", pm.response.json().data.tokens.accessToken);
  pm.environment.set("refreshToken", pm.response.json().data.tokens.refreshToken);
}
```

### Step 4: Subsequent Requests Use Token Automatically
All subsequent requests will include the token in headers automatically!

---

## FRONTEND JAVASCRIPT EXAMPLE

```javascript
// API Service with JWT
class ApiService {
  constructor(baseURL = 'http://localhost:5000/api') {
    this.baseURL = baseURL;
  }

  // Get token from localStorage
  getAccessToken() {
    return localStorage.getItem('accessToken');
  }

  getRefreshToken() {
    return localStorage.getItem('refreshToken');
  }

  // Store tokens
  setTokens(accessToken, refreshToken) {
    localStorage.setItem('accessToken', accessToken);
    localStorage.setItem('refreshToken', refreshToken);
  }

  // Clear tokens
  clearTokens() {
    localStorage.removeItem('accessToken');
    localStorage.removeItem('refreshToken');
  }

  // Make request with token
  async request(endpoint, options = {}) {
    const headers = {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      ...options.headers,
    };

    const token = this.getAccessToken();
    if (token) {
      headers['Authorization'] = `Bearer ${token}`;
    }

    try {
      const response = await fetch(`${this.baseURL}${endpoint}`, {
        ...options,
        headers,
      });

      if (response.status === 401) {
        // Token expired, try to refresh
        await this.refreshAccessToken();
        // Retry request
        return this.request(endpoint, options);
      }

      return response.json();
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Request failed:', error);
      throw error;
    }
  }

  // Auth methods
  async register(name, email, password, role) {
    return this.request('/auth/register', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify({ name, email, password, role }),
    });
  }

  async login(email, password) {
    const response = await this.request('/auth/login', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),
    });

    if (response.success) {
      this.setTokens(
        response.data.tokens.accessToken,
        response.data.tokens.refreshToken
      );
    }

    return response;
  }

  async getCurrentUser() {
    return this.request('/auth/me', { method: 'GET' });
  }

  async refreshAccessToken() {
    const refreshToken = this.getRefreshToken();
    if (!refreshToken) throw new Error('No refresh token available');

    const response = await this.request('/auth/refresh', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify({ refreshToken }),
    });

    if (response.success) {
      localStorage.setItem('accessToken', response.data.accessToken);
    }

    return response;
  }

  async logout() {
    await this.request('/auth/logout', { method: 'POST' });
    this.clearTokens();
  }

  // Protected API calls
  async getEquipment() {
    return this.request('/equipment', { method: 'GET' });
  }

  async createRequest(data) {
    return this.request('/maintenance-requests', {
      method: 'POST',
      body: JSON.stringify(data),
    });
  }
}

// Usage
const api = new ApiService();

// Login
await api.login('john.tech@gearguard.com', 'SecurePass123!');

// Use protected endpoints
const equipment = await api.getEquipment();
console.log(equipment);

// Logout
await api.logout();
```

---

## Security Checklist

- [ ] JWT_SECRET is set to a strong random value (32+ chars)
- [ ] JWT_REFRESH_SECRET is set to a different strong value
- [ ] .env is in .gitignore and not committed
- [ ] HTTPS is used in production
- [ ] Tokens are stored securely (localStorage/sessionStorage)
- [ ] Token refresh is implemented in frontend
- [ ] Automatic logout on token expiration
- [ ] Rate limiting on /auth/login endpoint
- [ ] Password validation enforced
- [ ] Deactivated users cannot login
